Protesting students at the Pretoria West campus blocked the entrance to the institution on Monday morning. Courtesy #DStv403 PRETORIA - It is unclear when academic activities will resume at Tshwane University of Technology’s main campus. Protesting students at the Pretoria West campus blocked the entrance to the institution on Monday morning. READ: Classes suspended at TUT amid protest Students say their grievances include alleged corruption at the university, NSFAS and accommodation issues. Students at TUT's main campus in Pretoria West have shut down academic activities in protest of what they say are irregular appointments of university council members. Courtesy #DStv403